# Dev rules for working on /web

Always use Docusuarus v3 conventions.

Use .mdx files always.

Avoid creating custom react components in .mdx files when docusuarus as a built in component that can function similarly.

Always use Ziinc as the author.

## Style Guide

Always be simple and to the point. Be concise and avoid duplications. Don't use the words "you".
Refer to @https://diataxis.fr/reference/ when writing documentation.

When writing a tutorial, refer to @https://diataxis.fr/tutorials/

When writing a guide, refer to @https://diataxis.fr/how-to-guides/

When writing explainer blog posts, refer to @https://diataxis.fr/explanation/

## Marketing Tone Guide
When explicitly asked to edit copy for a marketing component, use a fun and quirky tone that conveys a magical experience.